<paragraph id="3CD4D16D7824D9E64DCA638B929A7AE0" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="430FC0F6CC66C10A0F84E17657D8F4DB" LSID="9F726144-AA1B-D192-6588-270E23AFDA89" authority="Bonelli, 1810" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dyschirius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dyschirius Bonelli, 1810</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="60A76ADBE81C86997B7EAD626C65700C" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="36CB10D88CBEEF3D85B7C1F49F6CB2EE" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">
<taxonomicName id="0A340FA63DFC87C8FEF7A4EF9164CA80" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dyschirius</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1810: Tabula Synoptica. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="47F45894B09477F8E874B7659C1CD30A" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracicus">
<emphasis id="F2891EE3C75A542BD6A439F3A2381D40" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">Scarites thoracicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rossi, 1790 designated by Curtis (1831: plate 354). Etymology. Possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="FE10B6756EABDAD48FF8E085130646AA" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">dis</emphasis>
(twice, double) and 
<emphasis id="0BCCE6738272FB1B2866721973FE8DEC" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">cheiros</emphasis>
(hand), alluding to the presence of a curved spine laterally and a movable spur medially on the protibia of the adult [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2F1481753B2DEA0747AA6354146EBAE" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">
<taxonomicName id="DE4893E3B6227295D28E16ABBAD23498" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Dischirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dischirius</taxonomicName>
Duponchel, 1844: 151. Unjustified emendation of 
<taxonomicName id="9A94DC8B25A63331306922EF6F35E7E0" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B98C04FAABA4F4FAD11ED121FCB0CC88" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">Dyschirius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1810.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F77BDDF3D8F82899DED7E343F1E293D" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">
<taxonomicName id="6984B0FB9A8A58E27ED7DCC57602893A" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dyschiridius</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1941b: 260. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="C4984C425799555EB010C6E68B9FA810" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1827" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenosus">
<emphasis id="A9609136812554BEEEB830E235BCB352" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">Dyschirius arenosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1827 (= 
<taxonomicName id="8A0BE03FC545968BCAD623A95E29B032" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracicus">
<emphasis id="E97A9D6F3FA3FCBC2C86F6494AAF8202" italics="true" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">Scarites thoracicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rossi, 1790) by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3672C8487E6E888D0CFE0CD100FD619" pageId="292" pageNumber="293" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="6AE02DA0319EE1BEBFEFEAB2D18AC64B" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26AB0DAE069C77989B71E12A2D51BA55" pageId="292" pageNumber="293">About 245 species (Lorenz 2005: 151-154) in the Nearctic (about 60 species, one of them adventive), Neotropical (about 20 species, five shared with North America), Oriental (about 25 species), Palaearctic (about 140 species, many shared with the Oriental and Afrotropical Regions), and Afrotropical (about 30 species) Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3BF65C93D50140D1CEE0D6A0AE6EFF7B" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" type="identification">
<paragraph id="88A51257139E87B07C7641F7B00ACD69" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">
<pageBreakToken id="F322AB328C5E9E0CD2F06FA93D1DE0F7" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" start="start">Identification</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3700E33B05693716AA8F4A986123C289" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">
The North American species have never been revised. Bousquet (1988a) published a key to all species found in the area and briefly discussed each species-group. Subsequently five new species have been described by Bousquet (1997a) and Dajoz (2004), an adventive species has been detected (
<taxonomicName id="9BBBA2C19BC1D91A9F60CEB1FF66658C" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1784" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">
<emphasis id="5947C69EFA266BE1116B382A8D3F54C4" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius globosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in North America, two species have been treated as junior synonyms (
<taxonomicName id="7BA21180927759ECF285AF0080722FA9" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis id="BA78E3CFFEDCF57D622960306B798088" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="F8592A01AD498ED14C6890B4B917B9BC" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublaevis">
<emphasis id="1D19ED19BA51352FCB5EA4EC45F92B68" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius sublaevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5EE268B2CDF82FA1E9CF502F0E14992F" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="integer">
<emphasis id="C90A596386754D9CE9A9412580DC9FFE" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius integer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="EBAD350AE57176A06930F4470E337462" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dejeanii">
<emphasis id="27D182169CDD02D2BD651397FB833767" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius dejeanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and two species had their names changed (
<taxonomicName id="ED2A20E4D123A3AADAD326F316D25BC0" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1844" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis id="46C98CBA57E1D022B64A604AC7C2FA5C" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="EDDAF30E7579DFAD4CA9786E63CBB44E" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1867" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholicus">
<emphasis id="84553D4C406277DC1641D1D653F70565" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius melancholicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CEEFB20AA6753D824AF3F1CD2BC340E5" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="integer">
<emphasis id="311A4649593729D104899FAA89089D22" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius integer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="FC652407AF6DD5100EA8BC0EA9D716F1" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dejeanii">
<emphasis id="2E38EB6359389DB4EA1BFE359D3E1FA0" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius dejeanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D18C0BF9C4F1BE4CF0513E0C9D0D3FC9" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="23A579098AF435C7529EE09535B48BC7" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98F1EA3718F7C273BAD63F0AEAB737E8" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">
Fedorenko (1996) recognized two genera within 
<taxonomicName id="758943F175E7D0F4B5D31C5435D8E03B" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="15AB14451BDFAD70087B681DCB106796" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(minus 
<taxonomicName id="B809922B7EFC8C3791633662ABD5D6A0" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Akephorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDAEA9BAF872205066635D25A186EAE4" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Akephorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): 
<taxonomicName id="E707845E5C5822C1C351FFF16231244F" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="554F24F298AE6F9D067676C7B5D773A1" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with about 20 Palaearctic species and 
<taxonomicName id="084F0C6A11E7C187280E32EB3BC30EB1" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiriodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3F4C0DFCF8CBAB4B110371086590CED0" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschiriodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the remaining species. However, there seems to be no consistent character state that separates the two 
<normalizedToken id="2AD958627C0AF07B9CA6F72D4360235A" originalValue="“genera”">&quot;genera&quot;</normalizedToken>
except possibly for the basal sclerite of the endophallus which is &quot;strongly sclerotized&quot; in 
<taxonomicName id="263B903F9BEA851A1BF75247C9CE0041" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="31B2619F00C98C28AA8A579C7E1383C2" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and &quot;poorly sclerotized&quot; in 
<taxonomicName id="1A0C1639822246A4A5D59DDAEA05B688" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiriodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="989711B7422EF3531E81481E6004A5E8" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschiriodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition there is no solid evidence presented suggesting that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E44B812FD2A9E1B38BAADD1A226B222C" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A5CA2D0DCEA6BFE7FD470B81818FA34" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of authors is polyphyletic or that 
<taxonomicName id="1C2F313BB55FCFE66AB8A5DAFC1CA60E" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis id="666A9BEB9C58EC8DB83650468E4D7D11" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius sensu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fedorenko and 
<taxonomicName id="3F009E2E090D37612BD803F6DDF5A286" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiriodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B779BD829D6354033F2C7CEA2C8395F4" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschiriodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are sister-taxa. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="E886C0C0BB1CC91A6D0AA6F3282679A4" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sensu" subSpecies="auctorum">
<emphasis id="B25934B60ED960C3F1E3760F9D768572" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschirius sensu auctorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(prior to Fedorenko 1996) is a well-defined taxon and I see no reason to recognize 
<taxonomicName id="3D775F6CCAFB0BFBB94EFA9891A57998" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiriodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A413FB8DCD51DAAC4C046E78522DAFD" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschiriodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as generically distinct. A similar approach was adopted by Balkenohl (2003: 223-230) in the 
<emphasis id="939FF8625857027947C2FE595387FF28" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">
Catalogue of Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="10EB940A2A24F1D6A7C4CF7408815A1B" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Coleoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, Lorenz (2005: 151-154), and Erwin (2011b: 97-128).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE703A042BF94491369C416992D11F83" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">
Fedorenko (1996) recognized five subgenera within &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="3115D76B2ECE150B8D9A7D0651E90909" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschiriodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="293" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8DD41F11E9C5D32F3B07785C962439FB" italics="true" pageId="293" pageNumber="294">Dyschiriodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
:&quot; 
